# Security headers applied by the static host (Cloudflare Pages; Netlify uses the same
# convention — see docs/DEPLOYMENT.md for portability notes). The Content Security
# Policy itself is a per-page <meta> element generated by Astro (astro.config.mjs) so
# it holds on ANY host; only directives that browsers ignore in meta CSP live here.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
